{
  "texts": [
    "Experimental SettingsMethods.",
    "To assess the efficacy of various optimization strategies, we evaluate 11 representative GC methods categorized under 4 distinct optimization strategies: (1) gradient matching (GM)-based method: GCond, GCond-X [26], DosCond [54] and SGDD [31]; (2) distribution matching (DM)-based method: GCDM, GCDM-X [65] and SimGC [70];(3) KRR-based method: GC-SNTK and GC-SNTK-X [63]; (4) trajectory matching (TM)-based method: SFGC [29] and GCSR [62].",
    "Notice that the suffix \"-X\" represents the graphless variant.",
    "Given the diversity of evaluation criteria, GC methods are evaluated across various datasets with distinct characteristics, including three transductive datasets (Cora, Citeseer [97] and Ogbn-arxiv [98]), two inductive datasets (Flickr and Reddit [16]) and a dataset with sensitive feature (Pokec-n [94]).",
    "Implementations."
  ]
}